Ubuntu Terminal commands:
	
-------	unzip to unzip :)
	
-------	install .beb:
Using:

sudo dpkg -i /path/to/deb/file
sudo apt-get install -f

Using:

sudo apt install ./name.deb

Or

sudo apt install /path/to/package/name.deb


--------- network scan:
	nmap: first find your ip range with ifconfig, then: nmap 192.168.1.0/24

--------- ssh 
	for pi: ssh pi@ipaddress password standard = raspberry uname: pi

------- monitor hardware:
	htop

-------- files and mounts:

	pwd: shows working directory
	free: shows disk space
	df: shows all mounts and how much is used on each


-------- Download a whole homepage with wget
	
	something that worked for me: (after many many tries)
	
	wget --recursive --page-requisites --convert-links https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Learn/Front-end_web_developer
